Comments: BRAF V600E mutations in a low frequency of patients, perhaps more commonly in sporadic cases. Substantial diagnostic overlap between sporadic MPNST and the spindle-cell variant of melanoma.
Inactivating mutations of CDKN2A and/or CDKN2B and (at a lower frequency) of TP53 preferentially characterize MPNST and atypical neurofibromas

Germline LoF alongside somatic hotspot. Differential diagnosis to consider; DICER1 malignant teratoid tumour

loss-of-function mutations of genes encoding the core components of PRC2 found in the majority of conventional MPNSTs but not in their precursors. MPNSTs with PRC2 loss showed complete loss of trimethylation at lysine 27 of histone H3 (H3K27me3)
Biallelic inactivation of NF1 is present at high frequency both in conventional MPNSTs and in their benign precursors. NF1 are associated with worse event-free survival.

Epithelioid MPNSTs, distinct from conventional MPNSTs, are driven by SMARCB1 gene inactivation in about 80% of cases. Identical SMARCB1 alterations are also found in approximately 40% of epithelioid schwannomas, which are considered the putative precursors to epithelioid MPNSTs.

loss-of-function mutations of genes encoding the core components of PRC2 found in the majority of conventional MPNSTs but not in their precursors. MPNSTs with PRC2 loss showed complete loss of trimethylation at lysine 27 of histone H3 (H3K27me3). Structural alterations of the SUZ12 transcript previously reported.
